    <h2>Finding Help</h2>

    <p class='flow-text'>Support for victims and witnesses of hate crime and incidents.</p>

    <p>If you have experienced abuse or know someone who has, there are various organisations that can offer free and confidential support and advice. You can find more information and contact details on these websites:</p>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'Victim Support', 'https://www.victimsupport.org.uk', target: '_blank' %></h5>
      <p>Victim Support is the leading independent charity for people affected by crime in England and Wales. They are <strong>not</strong> a government agency or part of the police. Their services are free, confidential and available to anyone in England and Wales, regardless of whether you choose to report the crime or not or how long ago it happened.</p>
      <p><%= link_to 'Visit the website', 'https://www.victimsupport.org.uk', target: '_blank' %> or call the helpline on <strong>0300 303 1927</strong>. The helpline can give you details of your nearest branch and also put you in touch with local organisations that can help.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='divider'></div>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'Citizens Advice', 'https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk', target: '_blank' %></h5>
      <p>Citizens Advice provide free, confidential and independent advice from over 3,500 locations across the UK. These include high streets, community centres, doctors' surgeries, courts and prisons.</p>
      <p>Advice can be given in person, by phone, or by email. You can find contact details and your nearest citizens advice office on <%= link_to 'their website', 'https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk', target: '_blank' %>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='divider'></div>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'True Vision', 'http://www.report-it.org.uk/home', target: '_blank' %></h5>

      <p>True Vision is a police funded website designed to provide you with information about Hate Crime, including places to report it and where to get independent and confidential help. The website has an <%= link_to 'extensive list of organisations', 'http://www.report-it.org.uk/organisations_that_can_help', target: '_blank' %> that can provide information and support for all categories of hate crime.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>